The aviation safety paper proposes a novel, end-to-end framework that synergistically combines Large Language Models (LLMs) and Knowledge Graphs (KGs) to enhance the trustworthiness of safety analytics. This framework features a dual-phase pipeline: first, it automates the construction and dynamic updating of an Aviation Safety Knowledge Graph (ASKG) from multimodal sources using LLMs. Then, it utilizes this curated KG within a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) architecture to ground, validate, and explain LLM-generated responses, improving accuracy and traceability compared to LLM-only approaches.

