MM-Doc-R1 proposes the Similarity-based Policy Optimization (SPO) algorithm to address baseline estimation bias in multi-turn reinforcement learning (RL). SPO improves upon existing methods like GRPO by calculating a more accurate baseline through similarity-weighted averaging of rewards across multiple trajectories, rather than applying the initial state's baseline to all intermediate states. This approach enhances the stability and accuracy of the learning signal for agents, leading to superior training performance.

